com.alexgilleran.icesoap.parser.processor

Interface Processor<OutputType>

  • Type Parameters:
    OutputType - The type to output (and hence set as a field).

    public interface Processor<OutputType>
    Allows for the custom processing of a single field value - specifies one method process(String), in which input is taken in as a String (straight from the SOAP Envelope), this information is processed by implementation code, then the result is returned as an instance of the generic OutputType.
    Author:
    Alex Gilleran

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      OutputType process(String inputValue)
      Processes a raw value from a SOAPEnvelope (as a string) into the output value of the correct type.
